  "prompt": "Why does Airbnb disable accounts without any explanation?",
  "response": "Airbnb may disable accounts for various reasons, including:\n\n1. Potential policy violations\n- Suspected fraudulent activity\n- Repeated cancellations\n- Booking outside platform rules\n- Suspected fake reviews\n\n2. Security concerns\n- Suspicious login attempts\n- Potential identity verification issues\n- Account compromise risks\n\n3. Payment-related problems\n- Chargebacks\n- Payment method issues\n- Repeated declined transactions\n\n4. Community guideline breaches\n- Inappropriate communication\n- Violating host/guest standards\n- Negative interaction history\n\nWhile frustrating, Airbnb typically aims to protect users and maintain platform integrity. If your account is disabled, you can:\n\n- Contact Airbnb customer support\n- Request specific details about the suspension\n- Provide additional verification if needed\n- Appeal the decision with supporting documentation\n\nSpecific reasons are often not shared to prevent potential system manipulation.",
